                    <b>Compressor replacement cost </b>
                    <p><b>Symptoms: </b>The refrigerator is not cooling, making unusual or excessive noise, or starting and stopping frequently. <br>The compressor is the heart of your refrigerator's cooling system. A failing compressor is a significant issue and one of the most expensive repairs. </p>
                  </li>

                  <li>
                    <b>Thermostat replacement cost</b>
                    <p><b>Symptoms: </b>Fridge or freezer section is too warm or too cold, temperature fluctuations. <br>The thermostat controls the temperature inside the refrigerator. If it fails, it might not trigger the cooling process effectively. </p>
                  </li>

                  <li>
                    <b>Evaporator Fan replacement cost</b>
                    <p><b>Symptoms: </b>Poor cooling in the fridge section but freezer works fine, noisy operation. <br>The evaporator fan circulates cold air from the freezer to the fridge compartment. If this fan fails, the fridge may not cool adequately. </p>
                  </li>

                  <li>
                    <b>Condenser Fan replacement cost</b>
                    <p><b>Symptoms: </b>Refrigerator overheating, loud noise from the refrigerator back. <br>The condenser fan cools the compressor and condenser coils. If it's not working, the fridge can overheat or stop cooling. </p>
                  </li>

                  <li>
                    <b>Defrost Heater replacement cost</b>
                    <p><b>Symptoms: </b>Frost buildup in the freezer, freezer works but fridge section is warm. <br>The defrost heater prevents frost from accumulating in the freezer. Failure can lead to a build-up of ice and affect cooling. </p>
                  </li>

                  <li>
                    <b>Door Seal (Gasket) replacement cost</b>
                    <p><b>Symptoms: </b>Condensation or frost buildup near the door, energy waste. <br>A damaged door seal can allow cool air to escape, making your fridge work harder and increasing energy consumption. </p>
                  </li>

                  <li>
                    <b>Water Inlet Valve (for ice makers and water dispensers) replacement cost</b>
                    <p><b>Symptoms: </b>Ice maker not making ice, water dispenser not working. <br>This valve opens to supply water to the refrigerator's ice maker and dispenser. If it fails, these features won't work. </p>
                  </li>

